article.headline: Bradley 65, Wichita St. 50
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Dodie Dunson scored 18 points to lead Bradley to a 65-50 win over Wichita State on Wednesday night. Theron Wilson added 11 points for Bradley (13-8, 7-3 Missouri Valley), which led 30-25 at halftime. Wichita State (9-12, 3-7) went on a run to tie the game at 34 in the second half, but never led after the break. A 13-2 Bradley run put the game out of reach. Bradley outmuscled Wichita State, getting 18 second-chance points compared to 7 points for the Shockers and outrebounding 32-30. The Braves' defense held the Shockers to 35 percent shooting. Wichita State jumped out to a 12-5 lead to start the game, but faded as Bradley held the Shockers to 28 percent shooting in the first half. J.T. Durley led Wichita State with 12 points. Clevin Hannah added 10 points.
